span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/14/03 3:10:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=605.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Discussion for what we want for our skalds</span><hr size=1>  <br>
 Hi,<br>
<br>
  I would like to start a discussion on various ideas on improving skalds. I would like to debate whether these ideas are good/bad, overpowered or not enough of a fix for our class. <br>
<br>
 Skalds are vikings. I believe we should have more viking like abilities. In every realm except midgard, every class that starts out as a fighter type class gets the opportunity to spec shield. In midgard, every fighter type class gets the opportunity to either spec shield or receives advanced evade, except skalds. <br>
<br>
In my opinion, the hybrid abilities skalds receive do not make up for this large hole in our defense. The in combat group effecting abilities we have require us to be close to other melee group members. For us to contribute to our group in any meanful way we must fight along side the warriors, zerkers, thanes and savages. This usually leads to a quick death for us. Our offense is average for a hybrid. Our defense is subpar for a viking and our support abilities are far from making up for the lack of ability in the other two areas.<br>
<br>
These are the 3 ideas I like that would allow us to live longer in order for us to deliver what little support we do offer. They also give us a bit more utility or variety in the way we are allowed to spec.<br>
<br>
1. 2.0 spec and shield skill. Dmg add radius increase to the same as a paladins. Done<br>
<br>
  or<br>
<br>
2. 1.5 spec and shield skill added. Reduce cycle time on dd spells to 15 seconds. Power song added to songs lists. Dmg add radius increase to the same as a paladins. Done<br>
<br>
  or<br>
<br>
3. Advanced evade. Dodger added to RA. (remove mastery of blocking if needed.) Reduce cycle time on dd spells to 15 seconds. Power song added to songs lists. Dmg add radius increase to the same as a paladins. Move the mez immunity timer to spirit master timer instead of the healer timer. Done<br>
<br>
I've posted these ideas on the dev boards in this thread<br>
 <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=49950216&replies=225">vnboards.ign.com/message....eplies=225</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
After debating these ideas with the normal board trolls there I felt no one on the vn board could tear down my arguments. So I decided to take my ideas to the big leagues and see if the people who actually know about skalds could poke some holes in them. Please read the thread on the vn boards. Ya I know thats gonna be painful, heh. After your done come back take a crack at my ideas.  <p>Hooligan lvl 50 friar bedevere&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Frenn 50 skald bors&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Rhynn 45 healer bors</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilgour@teamskald>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/15/03 8:28:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=605.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald help...</span><hr size=1> OK, my input on this is also skewed.<br>
<br>
First, lets find out what the role of the skald is.  No one seems to know- even us.  If we are just to be taxi service, then we are fine as is... but not happy.<br>
<br>
If Midgard is to be truly the melee realm, lets augment our combat ability.  Either by, increasing our offence/defence or giving us more spec lines.  I disagree with a 1.5 spec with shield option- heck we cant make a good skald now.  With one more line, we dilute the advantages even further.  Make it shield plus 2 spec. Definitely evade 2. Possibly even a riposte line to make the parry somewhat useful.  Say a free attack on parry at no pluses to hit or damage.  Then people may spec more parry.  Allow us to do more spell interrupts, certainly Midgard is not able ot keep up with the caster heavy Alb or Hib at this point.  We had an entire attack force removed in 30 seconds by an equal number of alb casters.  About 30 people.  Not balanced by any means.<br>
<br>
If our role is support only, then make it support.  Not a hodgepodge of missed and dropping songs taken from the warden and minstrel lines.  (Actually, i dont remember who our hib counterpart is).  SO, if we are to be support, open up the songs so that we are something more than just a taxi.  Make it a shout AE mez, pbae mez or pbae shout damage, increase our song list to include a celerity, serenity, and/or end regen line.  Switch the mez to a 9 second stun.  Make it so that it is worthwhile to not spec the combat lines.  Also, stacking resist songs would be nice- as they are, no one plays them except in keep defence.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=svipdag@teamskald>Svipdag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/15/03 9:23:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=605.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skalds</span><hr size=1> The role of a Skald is that of a... Skald!<br>
<br>
No need to &quot;define our role&quot; or &quot;counterparts&quot;. We already have a &quot;theme&quot; about us. The typical word to describe a Skald is &quot;fast&quot;.<br>
<br>
And I don't mean &quot;running fast&quot;. We are<br>
<br>
- dealing Dmg fast (first Strike+dds)<br>
- are using our spells fast (everything is instant)<br>
- running fast (we do that, too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
- we make enemys even slower compared to ourselves<br>
<br>
Nearly all our abilities fit the theme of &quot;fast and hard&quot;. We don't need no Shield! It would not fit the skald theme, because we are not meant to &quot;make a stand&quot;. We are meant to charge singing into battle! Imho higher evade and/or dodger would suit the skald much better. Give us those, higher range on the battlesong and a good realm ability and we're done.<br>
<br>
And GIVE US A DECENT &quot;SHOUT&quot; SOUND! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hooliganfriar>hooliganfriar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/15/03 11:10:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=605.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skalds</span><hr size=1> Svipdag,<br>
<br>
What you are describing can already be done by a minstrel only better. A minstrel can zip in and dd and stun run away and stealth then start all over. They have better defense with evade 2 and gaining dex as they lvl. They also dont suffer in the support/utility area because of it. They do not lose the ability to spec stealth because of speed. Do you really want to be considered a subpar support rogue without stealth? Or would you rather become more like the class you started out as. A viking. The only reason we are led to believe we are vikings is because of our first trainer 50 lvls ago. Other hybrid classes are better defined in there base classes as they lvl. A warden still gains better buffs and heals as he lvls even tho he also gains melee ability. Why must we pay a penalty simply because we have speed? I still want to be a viking. <p>Hooligan lvl 50 friar bedevere&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Frenn 50 skald bors&lt;BR&gt;<br>
